> -static void __init fdt_init_reserved_mem_node(struct reserved_mem *rmem,
> -					      unsigned long node);
> +static void fdt_init_reserved_mem_node(unsigned long node, const char *uname,
> +				       phys_addr_t base, phys_addr_t size);

This isn't a bug, but the forward declaration appears to be missing the
__init attribute. Since the actual function definition still retains it,
could this cause section mismatch warnings during compilation?

