This isn't a bug, but is it necessary to set rmem->name to NULL here?
Since reserved_mem_count is not incremented on this error path, the next
region will logically discard this slot and unconditionally overwrite
rmem->name with its own uname.

Also, can this leak stale data to the next memory region?

If __reserved_mem_init_node() partially initializes the structure (such as
allocating memory and setting rmem->priv) before returning an error, those
pointers will remain in the rmem slot. Since the slot is reused for the
next region without being zeroed, the new region might inherit this
leftover state.

